 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-9: CLI thin client + CRDT sync + lifecycle (ADR-STORE-019, INV-MERGE-001). BACKGROUND: CLI detects daemon via socket, dispatches commands, falls back to embedded. CRDT periodic sync keeps daemon in sync with external disk writes (multi-agent). Lifecycle manages auto-start/stop. APPROACH: (1) CLI thin client (crates/braid/src/client.rs new): detect .braid/braid.sock, connect, serialize command as JSON, send, receive response, deserialize CommandOutput, print. Fallback to embedded on connection failure. Store-path validation: daemon reports its store path in ping response, CLI verifies match. (2) CRDT periodic sync: daemon background task every 10s lists txns/ directory, compares file set to known set, reads new files, applies via apply_tx, swaps ArcSwap. This IS merge (INV-MERGE-001) — set union of daemon store with disk store. No inotify. (3) Lifecycle: auto-start — CLI forks daemon if .braid/ exists but no socket. PID at .braid/braid.pid. 2h idle timeout (matching ST-1). SIGTERM -> graceful shutdown (flush W_alpha, write store.bin, remove socket/pid). Stale socket detection: if socket exists but not connectable, clean up and restart. (4) braid daemon {start,stop,status} subcommands for manual management. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid status works identically in daemon and embedded mode. (B) Fallback to embedded on daemon unavailability. (C) CRDT sync detects external txn files within 10s. (D) Daemon auto-starts on first command. (E) 2h idle shutdown. (F) Stale socket cleanup. (G) braid daemon status shows uptime, store size, F(S), commands served. DEPENDS-ON: CE-7 (daemon, t-451e387b), CE-8 (W_alpha, t-e545d28b). FILE: crates/braid/src/client.rs (new), crates/braid/src/daemon.rs, crates/braid/src/main.rs. TRACES-TO: ADR-STORE-019, INV-MERGE-001, INV-INTERFACE-008."
